# React Component Rule

- Use functional components with hooks.
- Follow Rules of Hooks strictly (no conditional hooks, stable call order).
- Keep components small and focused on a single responsibility.
- Prefer CSS modules for new component styling unless existing file conventions require otherwise.

## How to verify

- Confirm no class components are added.
- Confirm all hooks are called at top level of components or custom hooks.
- Confirm newly added component files are scoped in responsibility.
- Confirm styles are added via CSS modules when creating new component styles.
